  "doc_id": "30408",
  "text": "Other studies have focused on traumatic models by delivering loads to the spine via contact or non-contact forces; contact loading to the head is applied to simulate automotive and sporting events. These studies have determined fracture loads and described human neck injury tolerances [CITATION_1] . Inertial or non-contact loading is applicable to automotive rear impacts. Research in this area is mainly aimed at understanding whiplash-associated disorders. Tests using human cadaver models have delineated the role of demographic factors based on differences in intervertebral space and segmental kinematics [CITATION_2] . The insult is applied to the spine in one cycle in these traumatic loading events.",
